Honeywell HTF210B Quiet Set Personal Table Fan

The Honeywell QuietSet Slim Mini Tower Fan lets you adjust the cooling power by offering 4 levels of quiet operation. It features revolutionary QuietSet technology and a sleek design that won’t take up too much space in your home.

  • 4 Speed QuietSet Control
  • Oscillation
  • Automatic shut-off timer
  • 13-inch Table Fan
Read more



Honeywell Difference

Honeywell Fans enhance your environment by offering innovative designs that combine powerful air circulation with quiet operation.

Quietset Benefits

Honeywell QuietSet Stand Fans allow you to control both the sound and power levels. Set it, sit back, and enjoy - change the sound to just the right level when you're watching TV, sleeping, need white noise, etc. It also offers oscillation for times when you're not the only one relaxing.

Energy Savings

- Direct Current (DC) Motor Benefits uses up to 50% less energy than AC motors.

- Slim space saving design uses less plastic.

Product description

Color:Black

The Honeywell QuietSet Mini Tower Table Fan is a slim and compact model that's ideal for cooling small areas of personal space. The aspects of comfort and convenience can be observed with the inclusion of Advanced QuietSet Control that allows owners to personalize sound and cooling power. An easy-touch display and 2-8 hour auto off timer have also been incorporated for increased ease of use. This table fan also carries the additional bonus of saving you up to 50% energy as opposed to AC motors. The slim design of the Honeywell QuietSet Mini Tower Table Fan makes it a natural addition for desktops, nightstands and other areas of personal space.

1.0 out of 5 starsA great fan if you don't want your fan to actually move any air.
May 28, 2016
Color: BlackVerified Purchase
For the price of the fan and its size, this thing has such a narrow window of air movement that I can't believe it's a deliberate design. The tower is 13" tall, but only blows air across a 2.5 inch hole. With the fan sitting on my desk, about a foot to my left, I get blowing air on my shoulder. That's it.

Also, for a fan billed as a QuietSet, it's just as loud as cheaper desktop fans I've had in the past. At least those fans moved more air.

Incredibly disappointing, because I own a couple of Honeywell's large tower fans and they work wonderfully well.

Very disappointed.

I sit in a cubical and like a fan 2-3ft away to provide a light breeze. I've used numerous 'squirrel cage' fans. They generally last a year or 2 before the plastic bushings start to wear out and start getting noisy.

This Honeywell fan on its lowest setting was noisier than the fan I was replacing. And I'm not talking about an air movement constant 'white' noise. This was a weird 1 second 'brrddd', then a 1 second silence, 1 second 'brrddd', over and over. Sometimes I was able get this to go away with a whack... but then it eventually comes back.

Additionally, the Honeywell fan on its highest setting didn't blow as much air as my old fan on its lowest setting.

Justin Norton
5.0 out of 5 starsThat is not a bad thing at all because the product is very lightweight ...
June 18, 2018
Color: BlackVerified Purchase
Okay so, giving that I read all of the negative reviews, I was sure to be very careful with the product when I got it out of the packaging. The plastic is of course very cheap, but you get what you pay for. That is not a bad thing at all because the product is very lightweight and easy to move wherever you need it. Been using it and it's just amazing, and I use it just how I wanted it on my desk. It's been really hot lately, and although it doesn't cool off my ENTIRE room, I have a window unit for that when it does get too hot. The problem I was facing was that the window unit was just too loud when I tried recording videos or speaking into my Blue Yeti. Now that I have this it seems to be fairly quiet on the "White Noise" setting, and I just am in love with it. I suggest everyone be careful where you place this product, whether that be on your nightstand or your desk. One drop from this and you could lose a fan piece or something, so keep it in a large location where it won't really get knocked off. Every negative review here is because they are clumsy and knocked it off. If you just protect your product and follow all of the instructions then you're fine. Another tip is to use the timer thing because they did say there was a risk of a fire hazard or something, so be sure you use the timer thing and you don't have it ON 24/7. I have my timer set to 2 hours, and it will just be on for 2 hours then stop.

July 12, 2018
Color: BlackVerified Purchase
The picture of the fan is extremely misleading. It shows a 13 Inch Grill. Behind the grill is a 21/2 inch fan that is very low powered. The rest of the grill does NOT have air blowing from it, and, only air blows from the 21/2 inch bladed fan. The noise it makes is excessive, when considering the very small fan behind the grill. The DC electricity it advertises is from a small transformer, which gets warm. Electricity wasted by a transformer. It does oscillate as stated. The fan speeds are misleading with their wording, such as white noise, and so forth, as if it produces a special sound. The only sound is from the very small fan inside the tower. To note, for clarity, the tower does NOT have a blower, and, only has a small bladed fan, that does not blow air throughout the 13 inch grill. I am returning the fan.
